events.name: Penn State Nittany Lions at Alabama Crimson Tide

headlines.description: Trent Richardson ran for 144 yards in place of injured Heisman Trophy winner Mark Ingram, leading No. 1 Alabama to a 24-3 win over No. 18 Penn State on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Richardson, Bama dispatch Penn St.

events.name: Miami Hurricanes at Ohio State Buckeyes

headlines.description: Terrelle Pryor ran for 113 yards and a touchdown and passed for another Saturday and No. 2 Ohio State intercepted Jacory Harris four times in a 36-24 victory over 12th-ranked Miami on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pryor lifts Ohio St.; INTs burn Miami

events.name: Tennessee Tech Golden Eagles at TCU Horned Frogs

headlines.description: Matthew Tucker ran for two touchdowns, Andy Dalton threw for a score while setting another TCU record and the fourth-ranked Horned Frogs stretched their home winning streak to 15 games with a 62-7 victory over Tennessee Tech on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 4 TCU runs to 15th straight victory at home

events.name: Wyoming Cowboys at Texas Longhorns

headlines.description: Garrett Gilbert passed for 222 yards and a touchdown and No. 5 Texas shook off another slow start to beat Wyoming 34-7 Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 5 Texas shakes slow start, bests Wyoming

events.name: Idaho Vandals at Nebraska Cornhuskers

headlines.description: Taylor Martinez ran for 157 yards and two touchdowns, Nebraska's defense intercepted Nathan Enderle five times and sacked him seven times as the sixth-ranked Cornhuskers defeated Idaho 38-17 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Huskers pick on Idaho

events.name: Oregon Ducks at Tennessee Volunteers

headlines.description: LaMichael James ran for 134 yards, including a 72-yard touchdown, in his first game back after a one-game suspension and No. 7 Oregon scored 45 consecutive points to beat Tennessee 48-13 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ducks' James runs over Vols

events.name: South Florida Bulls at Florida Gators

headlines.description: Jeff Demps ran for a career-high 139 yards and a touchdown, Justin Trattou returned an interception for a score and No. 8 Florida beat South Florida 38-14 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Florida zaps USF

events.name: Iowa State Cyclones at Iowa Hawkeyes

headlines.description: Adam Robinson rushed for a career-high 156 yards and a touchdown on 14 carries as No. 9 Iowa crushed Iowa State 35-7 for its third straight win over the rival Cyclones.
headlines.shortLinkText: Iowa crushes ISU

events.name: Florida State Seminoles at Oklahoma Sooners

headlines.description: Landry Jones outplayed Christian Ponder by throwing for 380 yards and four touchdowns, and No. 10 Oklahoma moved past a shaky season opener with a 47-17 victory against No. 17 Florida State on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jones, No. 10 OU raze Noles

events.name: San Jose State Spartans at Wisconsin Badgers

headlines.description: John Clay ran for 137 yards and two touchdowns, and No. 11 Wisconsin beat San Jose State 27-14 on Saturday in a game overshadowed by the sight of teammate David Gilreath taken off the field on a stretcher.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clay lifts Wisconsin

events.name: James Madison Dukes at Virginia Tech Hokies

headlines.description: Drew Dudzik ran for two touchdowns and threw for another Saturday and James Madison stunned No. 13 Virginia Tech 21-16, the Hokies' second loss in six days.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 13 Hokies halted by JMU

events.name: Arkansas Razorbacks at Louisiana Monroe Warhawks

headlines.description: Ryan Mallett completed nine of 11 passes in the third quarter, leading to a touchdown and a field goal, and No. 14 Arkansas put away Louisiana Monroe 31-7 on Saturday after a sluggish first half.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mallett sharp in third to lead Arkansas in romp

events.name: Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets at Kansas Jayhawks

headlines.description: Jordan Webb threw three touchdown passes and Kansas rebounded from last week's humiliating loss to North Dakota State with a 28-25 upset of No. 15 Georgia Tech.
headlines.shortLinkText: KU upsets Ga. Tech

events.name: Virginia Cavaliers at USC Trojans

headlines.description: Matt Barkley threw first-half touchdown passes to Jordan Cameron and Brandon Carswell, and No. 16 Southern California hung on for a 17-14 victory over Virginia on Saturday night in Lane Kiffin's home head coaching debut.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 14 USC escapes UVa in Kiffin's home debut

events.name: LSU Tigers at Vanderbilt Commodores

headlines.description: Stevan Ridley scored a 65-yard touchdown and ran for 144 of his 159 yards in the second half, and 19th-ranked LSU never trailed in defeating Vanderbilt 27-3 Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ridley's big 2nd half trumps Vandy as LSU rolls

events.name: UNLV Rebels at Utah Utes

headlines.description: Terrance Cain passed for two touchdowns in his first start in almost a year and Shaky Smithson returned a punt 77 yards for a score as No. 20 Utah beat UNLV 38-10 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cain backs up No. 20 Utah's victory over UNLV

events.name: Georgia Bulldogs at South Carolina Gamecocks

headlines.description: Marcus Lattimore rushed for 182 yards and two first-half touchdowns and No. 24 South Carolina held off No. 22 Georgia 17-6 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 24 S. Carolina edges No. 22 UGA

events.name: Stanford Cardinal at UCLA Bruins

headlines.description: Andrew Luck threw two touchdown passes, and safety Michael Thomas scored on a 21-yard fumble return to lead the No. 25 Stanford Cardinal to a 35-0 win over the bumbling UCLA Bruins on Saturday night in the first game of the Pac-10 schedule.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luck's two TDs lead way as Stanford rips UCLA

events.name: Texas Southern Tigers at Connecticut Huskies

headlines.description: Jordan Todman ran for 151 yards and three touchdowns as Connecticut bounced back from a season-opening loss at Michigan by blowing out Texas Southern 62-3 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: UConn rolls past overmatched Texas Southern

events.name: Illinois State Redbirds at Northwestern Wildcats

headlines.description: Dan Persa threw two touchdown passes and ran for another score to lead Northwestern past Illinois State 37-3 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Persa drives Northwestern's early attack in rout

events.name: South Dakota Coyotes at Minnesota Golden Gophers

headlines.description: Dante Warren passed for 352 yards and three touchdowns for South Dakota and scampered for a 25-yard score on fourth-and-1 midway through the fourth quarter, sealing a 41-38 victory over Minnesota on Saturday.

headlines.description: Denard Robinson capped another electrifying performance Saturday by running for a 2-yard touchdown with 27 seconds left, sending Michigan to a 28-24 victory over Notre Dame.
